wwpLeosFilterMIB.name: wwpLeosFilterMIB

revisions.description: wwpLeosFilterProtocolType - IP protocol field is 8 bits, restrict syntax range to 0-255.

wwpLeosFilterMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpLeosFilterMIB.description: This MIB module defines the mgmt objects to support the protocol filtering on the WWP products.

wwpLeosFilterMaxHardwareResources.name: wwpLeosFilterMaxHardwareResources
wwpLeosFilterMaxHardwareResources.description: Specifies the maximum number of protocol filters resources this device supports.

wwpLeosFilterUsedHardwareResources.name: wwpLeosFilterUsedHardwareResources
wwpLeosFilterUsedHardwareResources.description: Specifies the total number of hardware filter resources currently used out of wwpLeosFilterMaxHardwareResources.

wwpLeosFilterCreated.name: wwpLeosFilterCreated
wwpLeosFilterCreated.description: The total number of filters currently created on the device.

wwpLeosFilterCountersMax.name: wwpLeosFilterCountersMax
wwpLeosFilterCountersMax.description: The total maximum number of counters supported on the device.

wwpLeosFilterCountersUsed.name: wwpLeosFilterCountersUsed
wwpLeosFilterCountersUsed.description: The total number of counters currently used on the device.

wwpLeosFilterTable.name: wwpLeosFilterTable
wwpLeosFilterTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the config parameters for the protocol filter.

wwpLeosFilterEntry.name: wwpLeosFilterEntry
wwpLeosFilterEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFilterTable.

wwpLeosFilterIndex.name: wwpLeosFilterIndex
wwpLeosFilterIndex.description: The index used in the table. It identifies the unique entry in the table.

wwpLeosFilterName.name: wwpLeosFilterName
wwpLeosFilterName.description: Specifies the name of the filter.

wwpLeosFilterAdminState.name: wwpLeosFilterAdminState
wwpLeosFilterAdminState.description: Specifies the admin state of the filter.

wwpLeosFilterOperState.name: wwpLeosFilterOperState
wwpLeosFilterOperState.description: Specifies the operational state of the filter.

wwpLeosFilterCounter.name: wwpLeosFilterCounter
wwpLeosFilterCounter.description: Specifies of counters for this filter need to be toggeled.

wwpLeosFilterStatus.name: wwpLeosFilterStatus
wwpLeosFilterStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'destroy'.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolTable.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolTable
wwpLeosFilterProtocolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the config parameters for the filter protocol table. Multiple Set operation must be performed on this table to create entries in the table. This table shows all protocols (standard and custom) protocols configured on the device.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolEntry.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolEntry
wwpLeosFilterProtocolEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFilterProtocolTable.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolIndex.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolIndex
wwpLeosFilterProtocolIndex.description: The protocol filter index used in the table. It uniquely identifies the entry in the wwpLeosFilterProtocolTable table.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolName.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolName
wwpLeosFilterProtocolName.description: Specifies the name of the protocol filter.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolType.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolType
wwpLeosFilterProtocolType.description: Specifies the protocol IP number associated with this entry.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolSrcPort.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolSrcPort
wwpLeosFilterProtocolSrcPort.description: Specifies the source port associated with this entry. If set to 0 means all ports.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolDstPort.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolDstPort
wwpLeosFilterProtocolDstPort.description: Specifies the destination port associated with this entry. If set to 0 means all ports.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolStatus.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolStatus
wwpLeosFilterProtocolStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must use multiple set operation to set all the following objects. wwpLeosFilterProtocolName, wwpLeosFilterProtocolIp, wwpLeosFilterProtocolSrcPort, wwpLeosFilterProtocolDstPort, wwpLeosFilterProtocolStatus. wwpLeosFilterProtocolStatus must be set to 'createandgo' to create entry. To delete and entry set this object to destroy.

wwpLeosFilterMemTable.name: wwpLeosFilterMemTable
wwpLeosFilterMemTable.description: The table lists the config parameters for the filter membership table.

wwpLeosFilterMemEntry.name: wwpLeosFilterMemEntry
wwpLeosFilterMemEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFilterMemTable.

wwpLeosFilterVlan.name: wwpLeosFilterVlan
wwpLeosFilterVlan.description: Specifies the vlan associated with this filter. It is also used as index in the table. if specified as 0 then it means all vlans.

wwpLeosFilterPortId.name: wwpLeosFilterPortId
wwpLeosFilterPortId.description: Specifies the port id associated with this filter. It is also used as index in the table. If wwpLeosFilterPortId is set to 0 then it means all ports.

wwpLeosFilterMemStatus.name: wwpLeosFilterMemStatus
wwpLeosFilterMemStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'destroy'.

wwpLeosFilterMemRule.name: wwpLeosFilterMemRule
wwpLeosFilterMemRule.description: Specifies rule to apply to this filter-vlan-port member -- block traffic or allow traffic. This value has a default value of block

wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemTable.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemTable
wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the config parameters for the filter-protocol membership table.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemEntry.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemEntry
wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemTable.

wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemStatus.name: wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemStatus
wwpLeosFilterProtocolMemStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'destroy'.

wwpLeosFilterStatsTable.name: wwpLeosFilterStatsTable
wwpLeosFilterStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table to view the stats of each filter entry.

wwpLeosFilterStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosFilterStatsEntry
wwpLeosFilterStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFilterStatsTable.

wwpLeosFilterDropBytes.name: wwpLeosFilterDropBytes
wwpLeosFilterDropBytes.description: The byte count dropped for this filter.
